==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
{{L.}} ''[[delphinus]]'', from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[δελφίν]]''' (''delphin''), a later form of the previous '''[[δελφίς]]''' (''delphis'') "a [[dolphin]]".

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Delphinus}}
'''Delphinus'''

#{{constellation}}: A small [[summer]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[dolphin]]. It lies between the constellations [[Cygnus]] and [[Aquila]].

